Governor of  Katsina State, Aminu Bello Masari  has sympathised with over 4,800 Internally Displayed Persons (IDPs) living in Faskari, Kadisau and Dandume, assuring them that as the military continues its operation the bandits would soon be rooted out and normalcy returned to their areas. The governor, who was speaking during his visit at the weekend, sympathised with the IDPs, and explained the need for total elimination of bandits to allow peace and normalcy to return to the areas. He added that the only language  the bandits understand was firing  AK 47, hence they will be treated with same language they understand. He assured that  about 4000 IDPs at Faskari Primary School and about 800 IDPs in Dandume would continue to receive proper attention and care through provision of adequate food and medical care throughout their stay in the camps. The governor further affirmed that the military and police deployed to deal with the bandits were able to secure the forests, and they would soon return to their respective houses to continue farming activities. In his remarks, the chairman of the state action committee on IDPs and commissioner of sports and youths development, Alhaji Sani Danlami, while appreciating the governor,  informed him that the committee had
been up and doing in feeding and giving  health care services to IDPs in the camps at Faskari and Dandume.